pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Air transportation workers/First-line supervisors of transportation & material-moving machine & vehicle operators/Production workers, all other

title: Aircraft pilots & flight engineers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Air transportation workers/Aircraft pilots & flight engineers/Production workers, all other

title: Airline pilots, copilots, & flight engineers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Air transportation workers/Aircraft pilots & flight engineers/Airline pilots, copilots, etc
Def: Pilot and navigate the flight of fixed-wing aircraft, usually on scheduled air carrier routes, for the transport of passengers and cargo. Requires Federal Air Transport certificate and rating for specific aircraft type used. Includes regional, national, and international airline pilots and flight instructors of airline pilots. Excludes “Electro-Mechanical and Mechatronics Technologists and Technicians” (17-3024).

title: Commercial pilots
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Air transportation workers/Aircraft pilots & flight engineers/Commercial pilots
Def: Pilot and navigate the flight of fixed-wing aircraft on nonscheduled air carrier routes, or helicopters. Requires Commercial Pilot certificate. Includes charter pilots with similar certification, and air ambulance and air tour pilots. Excludes regional, national, and international airline pilots. Excludes “Electro-Mechanical and Mechatronics Technologists and Technicians” (17-3024).

title: Air traffic controllers & airfield operations specialists
ttl: Air traffic controllers & airfield operations specialists
Level3: Air traffic controllers & airfield operations specialists
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Air transportation workers/Air traffic controllers & airfield operations specialists/Commercial pilots

title: Air traffic controllers
Level3: Air traffic controllers & airfield operations specialists
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Air transportation workers/Air traffic controllers & airfield operations specialists/Air traffic controllers
Def: Control air traffic on and within vicinity of airport, and movement of air traffic between altitude sectors and control centers, according to established procedures and policies. Authorize, regulate, and control commercial airline flights according to government or company regulations to expedite and ensure flight safety.

title: Airfield operations specialists
Level3: Air traffic controllers & airfield operations specialists
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Air transportation workers/Air traffic controllers & airfield operations specialists/Airfield operations specialists
Def: Ensure the safe takeoff and landing of commercial and military aircraft. Duties include coordination between air-traffic control and maintenance personnel, dispatching, using airfield landing and navigational aids, implementing airfield safety procedures, monitoring and maintaining flight records, and applying knowledge of weather information.

title: Flight attendants
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Air transportation workers/Flight attendants/Airfield operations specialists
Def: Monitor safety of the aircraft cabin. Provide services to airline passengers, explain safety information, serve food and beverages, and respond to emergency incidents.

title: Motor vehicle operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Flight attendants/Airfield operations specialists

title: Ambulance drivers & attendants, except emergency medical technicians
ttl: Ambulance drivers & attendants, except emergency medical technicians
Level3: Ambulance drivers & attendants, except emergency medical technicians
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Ambulance drivers & attendants, except emergency medical technicians/Airfield operations specialists
Def: Drive ambulance or assist ambulance driver in transporting sick, injured, or convalescent persons. Assist in lifting patients.

title: Bus drivers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Bus drivers/Airfield operations specialists

title: Bus drivers, transit & intercity
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Bus drivers/Bus drivers, transit & intercity
Def: Drive bus or motor coach, including regular route operations, charters, and private carriage. May assist passengers with baggage. May collect fares or tickets.

title: Bus drivers, school or special client
ttl: Bus drivers, school or special client
Level4: Bus drivers, school or special client
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Bus drivers/Bus drivers, school or special client

title: Driver/sales workers & truck drivers
Level4: Bus drivers, school or special client
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Driver/sales workers & truck drivers/Bus drivers, school or special client

title: Driver/sales workers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Driver/sales workers & truck drivers/Driver/sales workers
Def: Drive truck or other vehicle over established routes or within an established territory and sell or deliver goods, such as food products, including restaurant take-out items, or pick up or deliver items such as commercial laundry. May also take orders, collect payment, or stock merchandise at point of delivery. Excludes “Coin, Vending, and Amusement Machine Servicers and Repairers” (49-9091) and “Light Truck Drivers” (53-3033).

title: Heavy & tractor-trailer truck drivers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Driver/sales workers & truck drivers/Heavy & tractor-trailer truck drivers
Def: Drive a tractor-trailer combination or a truck with a capacity of at least 26,001 pounds Gross Vehicle Weight (GVW). May be required to unload truck. Requires commercial drivers’ license. Includes tow truck drivers. Excludes “Refuse and Recyclable Material Collectors” (53-7081).

title: Light truck or delivery services drivers
ttl: Light truck or delivery services drivers
Level4: Light truck or delivery services drivers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Driver/sales workers & truck drivers/Light truck or delivery services drivers

pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Taxi drivers & chauffeurs/Light truck or delivery services drivers

title: Motor vehicle operators, all other
Level4: Light truck or delivery services drivers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Motor vehicle operators/Motor vehicle operators, all other/Light truck or delivery services drivers
Def: All motor vehicle operators not listed separately.

title: Rail transportation workers
Level4: Light truck or delivery services drivers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Motor vehicle operators, all other/Light truck or delivery services drivers

title: Locomotive engineers & operators
Level4: Light truck or delivery services drivers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Locomotive engineers & operators/Light truck or delivery services drivers

title: Locomotive engineers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Locomotive engineers & operators/Locomotive engineers
Def: Drive electric, diesel-electric, steam, or gas-turbine-electric locomotives to transport passengers or freight. Interpret train orders, electronic or manual signals, and railroad rules and regulations. Excludes “Engineers” (17-2011 through 17-2199).

title: Locomotive firers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Locomotive engineers & operators/Locomotive firers

title: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, & hostlers
ttl: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
Level4: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Locomotive engineers & operators/Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
Def: Drive switching or other locomotive or dinkey engines within railroad yard, industrial plant, quarry, construction project, or similar location.

title: Railroad brake, signal, & switch operators
Level4: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Railroad brake, signal, etc/Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc

title: Railroad conductors & yardmasters
Level4: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Railroad conductors & yardmasters/Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
Def: Coordinate activities of switch-engine crew within railroad yard, industrial plant, or similar location. Conductors coordinate activities of train crew on passenger or freight trains. Yardmasters review train schedules and switching orders and coordinate activities of workers engaged in railroad traffic operations, such as the makeup or breakup of trains and yard switching.

title: Subway & streetcar operators
Level4: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Subway & streetcar operators/Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
Def: Operate subway or elevated suburban trains with no separate locomotive, or electric-powered streetcar, to transport passengers. May handle fares.

title: Rail transportation workers, all other
Level4: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Rail transportation workers/Rail transportation workers, all other/Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
Def: All rail transportation workers not listed separately.

title: Water transportation workers
Level4: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Water transportation workers/Rail transportation workers, all other/Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc

title: Sailors & marine oilers
Level4: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Water transportation workers/Sailors & marine oilers/Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
Def: Stand watch to look for obstructions in path of vessel, measure water depth, turn wheel on bridge, or use emergency equipment as directed by captain, mate, or pilot. Break out, rig, overhaul, and store cargo-handling gear, stationary rigging, and running gear. Perform a variety of maintenance tasks to preserve the painted surface of the ship and to maintain line and ship equipment. Must hold government-issued certification and tankerman certification when working aboard liquid-carrying vessels. Includes able seamen and ordinary seamen.

title: Ship & boat captains & operators
Level4: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Water transportation workers/Ship & boat captains & operators/Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc

title: Captains, mates, & pilots of water vessels
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Water transportation workers/Ship & boat captains & operators/Captains, mates, etc
Def: Command or supervise operations of ships and water vessels, such as tugboats and ferryboats. Required to hold license issued by U.S. Coast Guard. Excludes “Motorboat Operators” (53-5022).

title: Motorboat operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Water transportation workers/Ship & boat captains & operators/Motorboat operators
Def: Operate small motor-driven boats. May assist in navigational activities.

title: Ship engineers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Water transportation workers/Ship engineers/Motorboat operators
Def: Supervise and coordinate activities of crew engaged in operating and maintaining engines, boilers, deck machinery, and electrical, sanitary, and refrigeration equipment aboard ship. Excludes “Engineers” (17-2000).

title: Other transportation workers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Other transportation workers/Ship engineers/Motorboat operators

title: Bridge & lock tenders
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Other transportation workers/Bridge & lock tenders/Motorboat operators
Def: Operate and tend bridges, canal locks, and lighthouses to permit marine passage on inland waterways, near shores, and at danger points in waterway passages. May supervise such operations. Includes drawbridge operators, lock operators, and slip bridge operators.

title: Parking lot attendants
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Other transportation workers/Parking lot attendants/Motorboat operators

title: Automotive & watercraft service attendants
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Other transportation workers/Automotive & watercraft service attendants/Motorboat operators
Def: Service automobiles, buses, trucks, boats, and other automotive or marine vehicles with fuel, lubricants, and accessories. Collect payment for services and supplies. May lubricate vehicle, change motor oil, refill antifreeze, or replace lights or other accessories, such as windshield wiper blades or fan belts. May repair or replace tires. Excludes “Cashiers” (41-2011).

title: Traffic technicians
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Other transportation workers/Traffic technicians/Motorboat operators
Def: Conduct field studies to determine traffic volume, speed, effectiveness of signals, adequacy of lighting, and other factors influencing traffic conditions, under direction of traffic engineer.

title: Transportation inspectors
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Other transportation workers/Transportation inspectors/Motorboat operators
Def: Inspect equipment or goods in connection with the safe transport of cargo or people. Includes rail transportation inspectors, such as freight inspectors, rail inspectors, and other inspectors of transportation vehicles not elsewhere classified. Excludes “Transportation Security Screeners” (33-9093).

title: Transportation attendants, except flight attendants
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Other transportation workers/Transportation attendants, except flight attendants/Motorboat operators

title: Transportation workers, all other
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Other transportation workers/Transportation workers, all other/Motorboat operators
Def: All transportation workers not listed separately.

title: Material moving workers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Transportation workers, all other/Motorboat operators

title: Conveyor operators & tenders
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Conveyor operators & tenders/Motorboat operators
Def: Control or tend conveyors or conveyor systems that move materials or products to and from stockpiles, processing stations, departments, or vehicles. May control speed and routing of materials or products.

title: Crane & tower operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Crane & tower operators/Motorboat operators
Def: Operate mechanical boom and cable or tower and cable equipment to lift and move materials, machines, or products in many directions.

title: Dredge, excavating, & loading machine operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Dredge, excavating, etc/Motorboat operators

title: Dredge operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Dredge, excavating, etc/Dredge operators
Def: Operate dredge to remove sand, gravel, or other materials in order to excavate and maintain navigable channels in waterways.

title: Excavating & loading machine & dragline operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Dredge, excavating, etc/Excavating & loading machine & dragline operators

title: Loading machine operators, underground mining
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Dredge, excavating, etc/Loading machine operators, underground mining

title: Hoist & winch operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Hoist & winch operators/Loading machine operators, underground mining
Def: Operate or tend hoists or winches to lift and pull loads using power-operated cable equipment. Excludes “Crane and Tower Operators” (53-7021).

title: Industrial truck & tractor operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Industrial truck & tractor operators/Loading machine operators, underground mining
Def: Operate industrial trucks or tractors equipped to move materials around a warehouse, storage yard, factory, construction site, or similar location. Excludes “Logging Equipment Operators” (45-4022).

title: Laborers & material movers, hand
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Laborers & material movers, hand/Loading machine operators, underground mining

title: Cleaners of vehicles & equipment
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Laborers & material movers, hand/Cleaners of vehicles & equipment
Def: Wash or otherwise clean vehicles, machinery, and other equipment. Use such materials as water, cleaning agents, brushes, cloths, and hoses. Excludes “Janitors and Cleaners, Except Maids and Housekeeping Cleaners” (37-2011).

title: Laborers & freight, stock, & material movers, hand
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Laborers & material movers, hand/Laborers & freight, stock, etc

title: Machine feeders & offbearers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Laborers & material movers, hand/Machine feeders & offbearers
Def: Feed materials into or remove materials from machines or equipment that is automatic or tended by other workers.

title: Packers & packagers, hand
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Laborers & material movers, hand/Packers & packagers, hand

title: Pumping station operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Pumping station operators/Packers & packagers, hand

title: Gas compressor & gas pumping station operators
ttl: Gas compressor & gas pumping station operators
Level4: Gas compressor & gas pumping station operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Pumping station operators/Gas compressor & gas pumping station operators
Def: Operate steam-, gas-, electric motor-, or internal combustion-engine driven compressors. Transmit, compress, or recover gases, such as butane, nitrogen, hydrogen, and natural gas.

title: Pump operators, except wellhead pumpers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Pumping station operators/Pump operators, except wellhead pumpers
Def: Tend, control, or operate power-driven, stationary, or portable pumps and manifold systems to transfer gases, oil, other liquids, slurries, or powdered materials to and from various vessels and processes.

title: Wellhead pumpers
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Pumping station operators/Wellhead pumpers
Def: Operate power pumps and auxiliary equipment to produce flow of oil or gas from wells in oil field.

title: Refuse & recyclable material collectors
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Refuse & recyclable material collectors/Wellhead pumpers
Def: Collect and dump refuse or recyclable materials from containers into truck. May drive truck.

title: Mine shuttle car operators
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Mine shuttle car operators/Wellhead pumpers

title: Tank car, truck, & ship loaders
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Tank car, truck, etc/Wellhead pumpers
Def: Load and unload chemicals and bulk solids, such as coal, sand, and grain, into or from tank cars, trucks, or ships, using material moving equipment. May perform a variety of other tasks relating to shipment of products. May gauge or sample shipping tanks and test them for leaks.

title: Material moving workers, all other
pathString: Jobs/Transportation & material moving occupations/Material moving workers/Material moving workers, all other/Wellhead pumpers
Def: All material moving workers not listed separately.
